<TEXT>
 a cold war spy case landed a cia employee and his wife in prison.
 he's still behind bars, but her story has a different ending.
 bob glascoff has details in <TIMEX2 val="2000-10-21" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">today</TIMEX2>'s edition of "headliners."
<TURN>
 <TIMEX2 val="1994-10" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">october 1994</TIMEX2>, rosario ames is sentenced to <TIMEX2 val="P5Y" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="1994" anchor_dir="STARTING" comment="">five years in prison</TIMEX2> for helping her
 husband, cia turncoat aldrich ames, sell american secrets to the soviets.
 the colombia native met her <TIMEX2 val="FUTURE_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">future</TIMEX2> husband while working as a diplomat in
 mexico city.
 ames recruited her as an informant in <TIMEX2 val="1983" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">1983</TIMEX2>, then married her <TIMEX2 val="1985" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">two years later</TIMEX2>.
 during <TIMEX2 val="PAST_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="1985" anchor_dir="BEFORE" comment="This refers to the time that he met her through the time that he married her. Hard to pinpoint the meeting time.">that time</TIMEX2>, ames started passing information to moscow.
 the couple spent more than $1.5 million they received as payment on lavish
 jewelry, homes and cars.
 eventually, the cia caught on to their activities through electronic
 surveillance.
 aldrich ames admitted to espionage and tax evasion in order to get a more
 lenient sentence for his wife.
 she served <TIMEX2 val="P4Y" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">four years of a <TIMEX2 val="P5Y" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">five-year</TIMEX2> prison term</TIMEX2>.
 released <TIMEX2 val="1998" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">two years ago</TIMEX2>, she has since returned to colombia with their son.
 with "headliners," i'm bob glascoff.
</TEXT>
